# Next.js Data Handling Patterns

Enforce strict separation of data concerns and validation patterns in Next.js applications.

## Database Query Organization

All database queries must be organized into helper functions within the `src/db/queries` directory. Page components and Server Actions should NEVER contain direct database queries.

### Query Directory Structure
```
src/db/queries/
├── decks.ts      # All deck-related queries
├── cards.ts      # All card-related queries  
├── users.ts      # User profile queries (if needed)
└── index.ts      # Barrel exports (optional)
```

### Query Function Guidelines
- Each query file focuses on one main entity (decks, cards, etc.)
- All functions are async and return typed results
- Include user ownership verification in queries
- Use descriptive function names (e.g., `getUserDecks`, `getDeckWithCards`)
- Handle errors appropriately and return `null`/`undefined` for not found cases
- Always include TypeScript return types

### ✅ GOOD - Query Helper Functions
```typescript
// src/db/queries/decks.ts
import { db } from '@/db';
import { decks, cards } from '@/db/schema';
import { eq, desc, and } from 'drizzle-orm';
import type { Deck, Card } from '@/db/schema';

export async function getUserDecks(userId: string): Promise<Deck[]> {
  return db.select()
    .from(decks)
    .where(eq(decks.userId, userId))
    .orderBy(desc(decks.createdAt));
}

export async function getDeckById(deckId: string, userId: string): Promise<Deck | undefined> {
  const [deck] = await db.select()
    .from(decks)
    .where(and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.userId, userId)));
  
  return deck;
}

export async function getDeckWithCards(deckId: string, userId: string): Promise<{ deck: Deck; cards: Card[] } | null> {
  const deck = await getDeckById(deckId, userId);
  if (!deck) return null;

  const deckCards = await db.select()
    .from(cards)
    .where(eq(cards.deckId, deckId))
    .orderBy(desc(cards.createdAt));

  return { deck, cards: deckCards };
}

export async function createDeck(data: { title: string; description?: string; userId: string }): Promise<Deck> {
  const [newDeck] = await db.insert(decks)
    .values({
      title: data.title,
      description: data.description,
      userId: data.userId,
    })
    .returning();

  return newDeck;
}

export async function updateDeck(
  deckId: string, 
  userId: string, 
  updates: { title?: string; description?: string }
): Promise<Deck | null> {
  // Verify ownership
  const existingDeck = await getDeckById(deckId, userId);
  if (!existingDeck) return null;

  const [updatedDeck] = await db.update(decks)
    .set({
      ...updates,
      updatedAt: new Date(),
    })
    .where(eq(decks.id, deckId))
    .returning();

  return updatedDeck;
}

export async function deleteDeck(deckId: string, userId: string): Promise<boolean> {
  const existingDeck = await getDeckById(deckId, userId);
  if (!existingDeck) return false;

  await db.delete(decks).where(eq(decks.id, deckId));
  return true;
}
```

### ❌ BAD - Direct Database Queries in Pages/Actions
```typescript
// ❌ DON'T put database queries directly in pages or actions
// app/dashboard/page.tsx
export default async function DashboardPage() {
  const { userId } = auth();
  
  // ❌ Direct database query in page component
  const userDecks = await db.select()
    .from(decks)
    .where(eq(decks.userId, userId));

  return <div>{/* ... */}</div>;
}
```

## Data Retrieval: Server Components Only

All data fetching must happen in Server Components using query helper functions. Never fetch data in Client Components.

### ✅ GOOD - Server Component Using Query Helpers
```typescript
// app/dashboard/page.tsx
import { auth } from '@clerk/nextjs';
import { redirect } from 'next/navigation';
import { getUserDecks } from '@/db/queries/decks';

export default async function DashboardPage() {
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) redirect('/sign-in');

  // Use query helper function
  const userDecks = await getUserDecks(userId);

  return (
    <div>
      {userDecks.map(deck => <DeckCard key={deck.id} deck={deck} />)}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### ❌ BAD - Client Component Data Fetching
```typescript
// DON'T fetch data in Client Components
'use client';
import { useEffect, useState } from 'react';

export default function DashboardPage() {
  const [decks, setDecks] = useState([]);
  
  useEffect(() => {
    fetch('/api/decks').then(r => r.json()).then(setDecks); // ❌ BAD
  }, []);
}
```

## Data Mutations: Server Actions Only

All database writes (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE) must use Server Actions with proper validation and query helper functions.

### ✅ GOOD - Server Action with Query Helpers and Zod Validation
```typescript
// app/dashboard/actions.ts
'use server';
import { auth } from '@clerk/nextjs';
import { revalidatePath } from 'next/cache';
import { z } from 'zod';
import { createDeck, updateDeck, deleteDeck } from '@/db/queries/decks';

const CreateDeckSchema = z.object({
  title: z.string().min(1).max(100),
  description: z.string().max(500).optional(),
});

const UpdateDeckSchema = z.object({
  id: z.string().uuid(),
  title: z.string().min(1).max(100).optional(),
  description: z.string().max(500).optional(),
});

type CreateDeckInput = z.infer<typeof CreateDeckSchema>;
type UpdateDeckInput = z.infer<typeof UpdateDeckSchema>;

export async function createDeckAction(data: CreateDeckInput) {
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error('Unauthorized');

  // Validate with Zod
  const validatedData = CreateDeckSchema.parse(data);

  // Use query helper function
  const newDeck = await createDeck({
    ...validatedData,
    userId,
  });

  revalidatePath('/dashboard');
  return { success: true, deck: newDeck };
}

export async function updateDeckAction(data: UpdateDeckInput) {
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error('Unauthorized');

  const validatedData = UpdateDeckSchema.parse(data);
  const { id, ...updates } = validatedData;

  // Use query helper function
  const updatedDeck = await updateDeck(id, userId, updates);
  
  if (!updatedDeck) {
    throw new Error('Deck not found or access denied');
  }

  revalidatePath('/dashboard');
  return { success: true, deck: updatedDeck };
}

export async function deleteDeckAction(deckId: string) {
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error('Unauthorized');

  // Use query helper function
  const deleted = await deleteDeck(deckId, userId);
  
  if (!deleted) {
    throw new Error('Deck not found or access denied');
  }

  revalidatePath('/dashboard');
  return { success: true };
}
```

### ❌ BAD - Direct Database Queries in Server Actions
```typescript
// ❌ DON'T put direct database queries in Server Actions
'use server';
export async function createDeck(data: CreateDeckInput) {
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error('Unauthorized');

  // ❌ Direct database query in server action
  const [newDeck] = await db.insert(decks)
    .values({ ...data, userId })
    .returning();

  return { success: true, deck: newDeck };
}
```

### ❌ BAD - Using FormData Type
```typescript
// ❌ DON'T use FormData as the type
export async function createDeck(formData: FormData) {
  const title = formData.get('title') as string; // No validation
  // ...
}
```

### ❌ BAD - API Route for Mutations
```typescript
// ❌ DON'T use API routes for database mutations
// app/api/decks/route.ts
export async function POST(request: Request) {
  // Use Server Actions instead
}
```

## Zod Validation Requirements

All data inputs must be validated using Zod schemas with proper TypeScript types. Server Actions should use query helper functions for all database operations.

### ✅ GOOD - Comprehensive Zod Schema with Query Helpers
```typescript
// src/db/queries/cards.ts
import { db } from '@/db';
import { cards, decks } from '@/db/schema';
import { eq, and } from 'drizzle-orm';
import type { Card } from '@/db/schema';

export async function getCardById(cardId: string, userId: string): Promise<Card | undefined> {
  const [card] = await db.select()
    .from(cards)
    .innerJoin(decks, eq(cards.deckId, decks.id))
    .where(and(eq(cards.id, cardId), eq(decks.userId, userId)));
  
  return card?.cards;
}

export async function updateCard(
  cardId: string,
  userId: string,
  updates: { front?: string; back?: string; difficulty?: string }
): Promise<Card | null> {
  // Verify ownership through deck
  const existingCard = await getCardById(cardId, userId);
  if (!existingCard) return null;

  const [updatedCard] = await db.update(cards)
    .set({
      ...updates,
      updatedAt: new Date(),
    })
    .where(eq(cards.id, cardId))
    .returning();

  return updatedCard;
}

// app/dashboard/actions.ts
'use server';
import { auth } from '@clerk/nextjs';
import { revalidatePath } from 'next/cache';
import { z } from 'zod';
import { updateCard } from '@/db/queries/cards';

const UpdateCardSchema = z.object({
  id: z.string().uuid(),
  front: z.string().min(1, 'Front is required').max(1000),
  back: z.string().min(1, 'Back is required').max(1000),
  difficulty: z.enum(['easy', 'medium', 'hard']).optional(),
});

type UpdateCardInput = z.infer<typeof UpdateCardSchema>;

export async function updateCardAction(data: UpdateCardInput) {
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error('Unauthorized');

  const validatedData = UpdateCardSchema.parse(data);
  const { id, ...updates } = validatedData;
  
  // Use query helper function
  const updatedCard = await updateCard(id, userId, updates);

  if (!updatedCard) throw new Error('Card not found or access denied');

  revalidatePath('/dashboard');
  return { success: true, card: updatedCard };
}
```

### ❌ BAD - No Validation
```typescript
// ❌ DON'T skip validation
export async function updateCard(data: any) {
  // Direct database access without validation
  await db.update(cards).set(data);
}
```

## Client-Server Communication

Client Components must call Server Actions with validated data.

### ✅ GOOD - Client Component Using Server Action
```typescript
'use client';
import { createDeckAction } from './actions';
import { useState } from 'react';

export function CreateDeckForm() {
  const [isSubmitting, setIsSubmitting] = useState(false);

  async function handleSubmit(event: FormEvent<HTMLFormElement>) {
    event.preventDefault();
    setIsSubmitting(true);

    const formData = new FormData(event.currentTarget);
    const data = {
      title: formData.get('title') as string,
      description: formData.get('description') as string,
    };

    try {
      await createDeckAction(data); // Typed data, not FormData
      // Handle success
    } catch (error) {
      // Handle validation or server errors
    } finally {
      setIsSubmitting(false);
    }
  }

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit}>
      <input name="title" required />
      <textarea name="description" />
      <button type="submit" disabled={isSubmitting}>
        Create Deck
      </button>
    </form>
  );
}
```

## Client Component Separation

Interactive components that require `use client` (animations, state, event handlers) must always be extracted into separate Client Component files. Page files (`page.tsx`) and layout files (`layout.tsx`) must always remain Server Components.

### ✅ GOOD - Separated Client Component
```typescript
// app/dashboard/page.tsx (Server Component)
import { auth } from '@clerk/nextjs';
import { redirect } from 'next/navigation';
import { getUserDecks } from '@/db/queries/decks';
import { DecksList } from './DecksList'; // Client Component

export default async function DashboardPage() {
  const { userId } = auth();
  if (!userId) redirect('/sign-in');

  // Use query helper function
  const userDecks = await getUserDecks(userId);

  return (
    <main>
      <h1>Dashboard</h1>
      <DecksList decks={userDecks} />
    </main>
  );
}

// app/dashboard/DecksList.tsx (Client Component)
'use client';
import { useState } from 'react';
import type { Deck } from '@/db/schema';

interface DecksListProps {
  decks: Deck[];
}

export function DecksList({ decks }: DecksListProps) {
  const [filter, setFilter] = useState('');
  const [isAnimating, setIsAnimating] = useState(false);

  const filteredDecks = decks.filter(deck => 
    deck.title.toLowerCase().includes(filter.toLowerCase())
  );

  const handleCardClick = (deckId: string) => {
    setIsAnimating(true);
    // Handle click logic
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <input
        type="text"
        placeholder="Filter decks..."
        value={filter}
        onChange={(e) => setFilter(e.target.value)}
      />
      <div className={isAnimating ? 'animate-pulse' : ''}>
        {filteredDecks.map(deck => (
          <div key={deck.id} onClick={() => handleCardClick(deck.id)}>
            {deck.title}
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### ❌ BAD - Page with use client
```typescript
// ❌ DON'T add 'use client' to page files
'use client';
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';

export default function DashboardPage() {
  const [decks, setDecks] = useState([]);
  const [filter, setFilter] = useState('');

  useEffect(() => {
    fetch('/api/decks').then(r => r.json()).then(setDecks);
  }, []);

  return (
    <div>
      <input 
        value={filter} 
        onChange={(e) => setFilter(e.target.value)} 
      />
      {/* Page logic mixed with client state */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### ❌ BAD - Layout with use client
```typescript
// ❌ DON'T add 'use client' to layout files
'use client';
import { useState } from 'react';

export default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  const [theme, setTheme] = useState('light');

  return (
    <html>
      <body>
        <button onClick={() => setTheme(theme === 'light' ? 'dark' : 'light')}>
          Toggle Theme
        </button>
        {children}
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

### ✅ GOOD - Layout with Extracted Client Component
```typescript
// app/layout.tsx (Server Component)
import { ThemeProvider } from './ThemeProvider';

export default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <html>
      <body>
        <ThemeProvider>
          {children}
        </ThemeProvider>
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}

// app/ThemeProvider.tsx (Client Component)
'use client';
import { useState, createContext, useContext } from 'react';

export function ThemeProvider({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  const [theme, setTheme] = useState('light');

  return (
    <div className={theme}>
      <button onClick={() => setTheme(theme === 'light' ? 'dark' : 'light')}>
        Toggle Theme
      </button>
      {children}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Summary Checklist

- [ ] All database queries organized in `src/db/queries` helper functions
- [ ] Page components NEVER contain direct database queries
- [ ] Server Actions NEVER contain direct database queries  
- [ ] Data fetching only in Server Components using query helpers
- [ ] Database mutations only via Server Actions using query helpers
- [ ] All inputs validated with Zod schemas
- [ ] TypeScript types for Server Action parameters (not FormData)
- [ ] User authentication checked in all Server Actions
- [ ] Ownership verification handled in query helper functions
- [ ] Proper error handling with validation feedback
- [ ] `revalidatePath()` called after mutations
- [ ] Interactive components extracted into separate Client Component files
- [ ] Page files (`page.tsx`) remain Server Components (no `use client`)
- [ ] Layout files (`layout.tsx`) remain Server Components (no `use client`)
- [ ] Server data passed as props to Client Components